    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tools used in beekeeping. These have long metal blades, most often with wooden handles, and are used for the removal of the wax cover over a frame of honey prior to extraction. The blade is heated either electrically or via another heat source such as hot water.</Note_Text>
